<h1 style="text-align: center;">Professional Planning Programs</h1>
<p style="text-align: left;">For those motivated students and families who wish to go beyond self-help tools, we offer one-to-one consultation with our team of experienced professionals who will help you put together a comprehensive plan for finding the best-fit school and cutting the cost of attending college.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">G. Mike Crawford</span></strong> analyzes the family&rsquo;s finances and meets with the parents and students to explain how they can achieve the lowest possible college costs based upon their unique situation. In addition to explaining the complicated world of the university financial aid system, Mike develops a custom financial plan for the family to help them properly use their assets, manage cash flow, and make legal use of the tax code to pay less for college.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Craig Rider</span> </strong>helps students discover their unique gifts and strengths and apply them to their course of study and choice of a prospective career. He administers multiple standard assessments and presents a written report with professional interpretation of the findings. In conference with the student and parents, Craig helps them apply the findings to the student&rsquo;s academic and career decisions.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Allen Hye</span></strong> conducts a detailed interview, assesses the student&rsquo;s criteria in choosing a college, and researches the colleges that best match those criteria. He provides a written report explaining which schools would be an excellent &ldquo;fit&rdquo; for the student, and why. Allen further recommends how the student can most effectively connect with the colleges and thrive there once a choice has been made.</p>
